      "comment_id" : 60140574,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "It&#39;s probably a bug in the ReST service.  They&#39;re probably not expected the <code>charset</code> to be set in the Content-Type.  My guess is that they&#39;re checking if the string <code>&quot;application&#47;json; charset=utf-8&quot; == &quot;application&#47;json&quot;</code>.  That being said, JSON must be utf-8 so it&#39;s perfectly valid to leave out the charset."
    }, {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 219257,
        "reputation" : 11503,
        "user_id" : 476048,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "accept_rate" : 72,
        "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/dhByN.jpg?s=256",
        "display_name" : "Berin Loritsch",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/476048/berin-loritsch"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 42,
      "creation_date" : 1499362410,
      "post_id" : 22643964,
      "comment_id" : 76886471,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Because <code>charset=utf8</code> is not a valid character set designation.  The correct version would be <code>charset=utf-8</code>.  The dash is important.  The list of valid character set designations is managed by IANA RFC2879: <a href=\"http://www.iana.org/assignments/character-sets/character-sets.xhtml\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">iana.org/assignments/character-sets/character-sets.xhtml</a>"
    }, {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 1805635,
        "reputation" : 3227,
        "user_id" : 1642766,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "accept_rate" : 60,
        "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/0747066ea5cbebf9a352f776d8f6ef5a?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
        "display_name" : "Salman",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1642766/salman"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 1,
      "creation_date" : 1525689744,
      "post_id" : 22643964,
      "comment_id" : 87441448,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "Wasted a whole lot of time trying different things and then tried removing the charset=utf8 and it worked. Thanks."
    }, {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 332090,
        "reputation" : 2047,
        "user_id" : 657174,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/c15b3696c74113aebc764c3b878bce66?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
